Famous proprietary traders have included Steven A. Cohen, Daniel Och, and Boaz Weinstein. Some of the investment banks most historically associated with trading was Salomon Brothers and Drexel Burnham Lambert, and currently Goldman Sachs. \nNick Leeson took down Barings Bank with unauthorized proprietary positions.  Another trader, Brian Hunter, brought down the hedge fund Amaranth Advisors when his massive positions in natural gas futures went bad.